        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When using Zend_Paginator_Adapter_Null, Zend_Paginator::_pages->lastItemNumber is set incorrectly. This is because Zend_Paginator_Adapter_Null::getItems() returns an empty array, which Zend_Paginator::getItemsByPage() casts to an empty ArrayIterator, which, in turn, sets Zend_Paginator::_pages->lastItemNumber to an incorrect number. Shouldn't Zend_Paginator_Adapter_Null::getItems() return an array containing the number of empty values equal to Zend_Paginator_Adapter_Null::_count ? Am I overlooking something?\n\nHere's a patch:\n\nIndex: Paginator\/Adapter\/Null.php\n===================================================================\n--- Paginator\/Adapter\/Null.php\t(revision 10727)\n+++ Paginator\/Adapter\/Null.php\t(working copy)\n@@ -58,7 +58,7 @@\n      *\/\n     public function getItems($offset, $itemCountPerPage)\n     {\n-        return array();\n+        return array_slice(array_fill(0, $this->_count, ''), $offset, $itemCountPerPage);\n     }\n \n     \/**\n"
        },
